[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dependency needs**\n\nI see that the DefaultPlexusContainer requires Guice to function properly, but the upstream tests already add Guice. I'm wondering if we really need that dependency, especially since normal direct tests might not utilize the container. It seems that meaningful use with injection will definitely need Guice. There's the option of using reflection, but the default container feels more standard. I guess I should check if we need to add a specific version of Guice, like 6.0.0. Let's run some tests with Guice and APT to get clarity.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_01e7144624fa1af1016a3f31d28a308190a1e1fdedaea6a58c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPzHV4_BT88-NDFV2AP4VNohL1G43ijmIkgOv3JF0D1oMlKE6F_U8r50Bh8r_hK5TmrYN12UkW3dA2Q7O-l_-zx0WjaRMSLdDhYhQJ2Mltx80mxQ1uO3Kl_ZZaDYISVt4C7CzSDg6Sc-LXPMdCIB_VnW3SQ_j--l6EFOwhSIz80hpngfFHrx24WtfsUCQ5ET0UDBjQ3Q9G031XE9ynOle8YOA2fsVeelnYT2C5ARtzKGZDU9-uYwGJ8s-hE2XX74YrAti3h72oFBhM5W23N2W3-_jyohMPeV4IWsV_8rTnP4v8mxdlK5GjlLfFT7kdxlyYc5Hoc3WkNJVn4kR87lVgLv7jJxQNhUXnWLlmaYNbfoR4m9tBLR-WzbNR_3nuMdQVEtXSSthJ3hUooVFJjfFYnY6vAIODsjBmgyhPsyv97UuHIK0umKy0bydBUU48NpA42GyxLkYdnhkfkTG8o2p4oLnANflMRjopRGezXiKnu0AfvhmAwBIFG5J_nOjY3lJdtxD9vEgxAr5ThqFaNqGXUG0S1mB1JT7TLez6JxzVIz4Zo_-HgWGjvlRLWQbcjr6bugM7SkKHQD2WJ3zHFvdpkW7d0E2a70URLqw_gN0UkX23ZyQNTdToLuVDh9pxuPdGQe3y_82kD1zyhn7HB26PgnEMJd1j99SgCEuw47joJYWHhuZjUNE_kS_YpRUibJJKaxSjE7XkrD4O9_z24dwCzPofv5Vk563R1qtdz3Y-MkTDANxeMzJnBiif4czFUs18KjsYfW0fm8-RJv5cNPq3Lxtl5Movsq0OlYwVdxfZxU0g80j37bfNCkY2fEtKif22grZxDgDpe8UN5pzeJ-5Gv8L7472dtqqdcDkFmqHtK3zsCJFcKAXiFgDAS7eQGG_G4hmwhKW12C6eBhoOtYSjB4zSErlcEn8ky24RUIBE4q2sBo_CZdkvw4EuD5KcbPdNzhWS5lDFMmifVTNKcxKItfOzYkMymLdb2f9UjTA5BD4t6BY4g5-Sd2yCeiwhN959RB8lhvlKKsDCso75Lp4iBUDCWzDrAryvIBUi0rBYJFdkq_HguWLI9t3x-5Cp4rOi0Abh0jaNWG6hLPCm_f5pMapdsCl8YwT0ddzEzOjpRfS_YQI3UtpWAomf9doZVeX7K5bmJvi9H9wYx