a public API for the skin, but maybe not if tests avoid skin. We’ll focus on a minimal set of dependencies to ensure meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering skin-renderer coverage**\\n\\nI’m thinking that achieving meaningful skin-renderer coverage might necessitate the inclusion of certain dependencies. Specifically, I should consider `org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0` as a test implementation, since the Doxia parser modules are no longer part of the core. The upstream POM indicates that module dependencies need to be specified for the component descriptor. I might also consider including xdoc or fml, but for now, apt should suffice for meaningful formatting.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering API risks**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential risks associated with the API changing in version 1.9.1. I wonder if the provided dependency could hide any missing Maven runtime details. It’s essential to keep track of that! Alternatively, I need to structure the final output as JSON with `action: \\\"advisory_preparation\\\"` and a summary. I need to ensure it’s strictly JSON, avoiding any markdown formatting. Keeping things clear is key!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0 exposes Maven Artifact skin APIs via a provided dependency and no longer bundles several Doxia parser modules needed to exercise normal site-source rendering.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"doxia-site-renderer declares maven-artifact as provided, but public skin/context APIs use org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact and DefaultArtifact; Gradle tests will not receive it transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"upstream 2.0.0 notes Doxia modules are no longer in doxia-core and must be stated explicitly so parser component descriptors are available for rendering APT site sources.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties appear required. The 2.0.0 API differs from 1.9.1: RenderingContext and SkinResourceLoader are gone; use DocumentRenderingContext and the current SiteRenderingContext API. DefaultSiteRenderer has injected collaborators, so meaningful render/locate coverage should use component-style setup or otherwise initialize collaborators rather than assuming direct construction covers the rendering path.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.9.1 tests are API-incompatible with 2.0.0 and must be rewritten rather than mechanically version-bumped.\",\n    \"If tests cover additional source formats such as xdoc or fml, matching doxia-module-xdoc or doxia-module-fml test dependencies may also be needed.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01e7144624fa1af1016a3f31fcb40081908840b3ec133c6cd9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1524, "output": 1197, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48801, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782526447911, "responseId": "resp_01e7144624fa1af1016a3f31f08ecc8190b4ec0bf6ab762926"}, "toolResults": []}
